					<H1 align="center"><font color="#000080" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong> <font size="3" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">
									The 2006 SCCA and California Rally Series Rally School</font></strong><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><FONT size="3">&nbsp;</FONT><b><span lang="en-us"><br>
  June 10-11, 2006<br>
Willows, California<BR><BR><A href="http://www.sfrscca.org/RallyX/rallyschool2006entry.html"><FONT size="3">Entry Form</FONT></A>
</span></b> </font></font>
					</H1>
					<H1 align="center"><FONT face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#000080"><FONT face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><B><SPAN lang="en-us"><FONT size="1">Rally 
											School Contact: </FONT><A href="mailto:rally@grok.com"><FONT size="1">Michel 
												Hoche-Mong</FONT></A></H1>
					</SPAN></B></FONT></FONT>
					<p align="center"><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><img src="http://www.sfrscca.org/RallyX/images/sfr_logo.jpg" width="160" height="100"
								border="0"><img src="http://www.sfrscca.org/RallyX/images/presented_by_subaru.jpg" width="278" height="100"><img src="http://www.sfrscca.org/RallyX/images/crs.jpg" width="94" height="100"></font></p>
					<h2><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>The Rally School</strong></font></h2>
					<p><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">A daylong event that 
						covers all elements of rally competition. Again this year, a heavy emphasis 
						will be placed on in the seat time for both drivers and co-drivers on practice 
						courses designed to give them the "feel" of real competition. Completion of the 
						school satisfies the requirement for a "first timers" class at the student's 
						first event. This is a great opportunity to show a new co-driver, service crew 
						member, or spouse what rally is all about. There is no one involved in the 
						sport that will not benefit from this workshop. Your entry includes a "working 
						sack lunch" Saturday afternoon (the learning continues over the munching) and 
						pizza buffet Saturday night. You do not need to bring any vehicle to take part 
						in the classroom part of the course. You may use any reasonable street 
						automobile, except convertibles, for the drivers practice sessions as they are 
						on the same smooth dirt lot as the Sunday RallyCross. Experienced Drivers will 
						ride along with you to show you how to use the practice area. Two or more 
						students may share one car. A helmet with a Snell 95 or newer sticker is 
						required for the driver's practice. A few loaner helmets are available. No 
						helmets are required for the co-driver practice sessions.</p>
					<H2><FONT face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><STRONG>Elidgible Vehicles 
								and Classes</STRONG></FONT></H2>
					<P><FONT face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1"><FONT face="Verdana" size="1"><FONT face="Verdana" size="1">This&nbsp;event 
									is open to any fixed-roof production based vehicle (including convertibles with 
									a factory hardtop attached, targa-types with factory panel in place, t-tops 
									with factory panels in place) that can pass <A href="http://www.sfrscca.org/RallyX/?faq#Tech">
										safety inspection</A>. However, if the Safety Steward determines at his/her 
									discretion that a vehicle cannot readily negotiate the course, it may be 
									excluded. Sport Utility Vehicles and trucks <STRONG><U>are required</U></STRONG>
									to have full roll cages and are subject to the approval of the Safety Steward. 
									Soft-top convertibles are <STRONG><U>not allowed</U></STRONG>.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
					<P><FONT face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1"><FONT face="Verdana" size="1">
								There are new SCCA RallyCross Classes for 2006 and are discussed <A href="http://www.sfrscca.org/RallyX/?faq#Classes">
									in our FAQ</A>.</FONT></FONT><FONT face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
					</FONT>
					<h2><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>The RallyCross</strong></font></h2>
					<p><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">A RallyCross or RallyX 
							is similar to an autocross or solo except that it is held on a dirt lot. This 
							event combines the skills of rally driving with the strategy and techniques of 
							solo. The exciting aspect of this new class of events is that stock street 
							vehicles will be allowed to compete. Classes will be established for prepared 
							and street stock vehicles. The only safety equipment required is stock or 
							better seatbelts and a helmet with a Snell 95 or newer sticker is required. A 
							few loaner helmets are available. The RallyCross will be a part of the 2006 
							California Rally Series Rally Cross Championship. The event will be held at <A href="http://www.thunderhill.com/">
								Thunderhill Raceway Park</A> in Willows, CA. All CRS RallyCross classes 
							will be offered. See the entry form for complete details. Club memberships or 
							rally licenses are not required. Open top, or convertible vehicles may not be 
							used driving practice or the RallyX. </font>
					</p>
					<h2><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Driving Practice and 
							RallyCross Location and Surface</font></h2>
					<P><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> The drivers practice 
							for the school and the RallyCross are held in a dirt lot at Thunderhill Raceway 
							Park (see below for directions). The course is reasonably hard packed and 
							smooth, but will get cut up during the course of the day so the course will be 
							regraded periodically and watered to keep the dust down. There is some gravel 
							and rock in the dirt surface but experience has shown that damage from this 
							surface is minimal. Porta Potties will be available, and food is available both 
							at the racetrack and at a variety of fast food establishments in Willows, 7 
							miles away. Open top or convertible vehicles may not be used driving practice 
							or the RallyCross.</font></P>
					<P><FONT face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1"><FONT size="2"><STRONG><FONT face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Event 
										Location</FONT> </STRONG>
					</P>
					<P></P>
					<P><FONT face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1"><STRONG>Willows, California<BR>
							</STRONG>Willows is located just off Hwy 5, about 100 miles North of the San 
							Francisco Bay Area, due west of Chico. <A href="http://www.thunderhill.com/html/lodging.html">
								Click here for lodging</A>. Ask specifically for the "Thunderhill rate" 
							when checking rates.<BR>
							<FONT face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1">
								<BR>
								<STRONG>Monday Afternoon Club<BR>
									120 N Lassen<BR>
									Willows, CA<BR>
								</STRONG>The school begins at the Monday Afternoon Club. <A href="http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;hl=en&amp;q=120+N+Lassen,+Willows,+CA&amp;om=1">
									Click here for directions</A>.<BR>
								<BR>
								<STRONG>Thunderhill Raceway Park<BR>
									5205 Hwy 162<BR>
									Willows, CA<BR>
								</STRONG>In-car session and Sunday's RallyCross event will be held at 
								Thunderhill, which </FONT></FONT><FONT face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1">
							is located in the foothills 7 miles west of Willows. <A href="http://www.thunderhill.com/html/location.html">
								Click here for directions</A>.</FONT></P>
					<P></FONT></FONT><FONT face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1"><FONT size="2"><STRONG>Event 
									Dates and Schedule</STRONG></FONT></FONT></P>
					<P><FONT face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1"><B>Rally School Schedule</B></FONT></P>
					<p><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b><u><em>Saturday, June 10</em></u><br>
								<br>
								7:30 School Registration at the Monday Afternoon Club<br>
								8:15 Welcome - Paula Gibeault
								<br>
								8:30 Performance Rallying Overview - Paula Gibeault<br>
								9:15 Basic Controls and Timing - TBA<br>
								10:15 Control Walk Through
								<br>
								11:00 Beginning Driving Talk I - Mike Gibeault<br>
								12:00 Break and grab Bag Lunch<br>
								12:15 Basic Course Following and Safety Items - TBA<br>
								1:15 Basic Car Prep - TBA<br>
								1:45 Beginning Driving Talk II - Mike Gibeault<br>
								2:30 Team Management - Paula Gibeault</b></font></p>
					<p><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b>Breakout Sessions</b></font></p>
					<p><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b> Drivers<br>
								2:45 Practice Session Prep<br>
								3:15 Leave for Thunderhill
								<br>
								3:30 Car Walk Around and In-Car Driving Practice<br>
								6:30 Leave Thunderhill<br>
								7:00 Pizza dinner </b></font>
					</p>
					<p><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b> Co-Drivers<br>
								2:45 In Car Practice, Video, and discussion<br>
								5:45 Advanced Co-Driving - Gibeault, Dillon<br>
								7:00 Pizza dinner </b></font>
					</p>
					<p>
						<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b><u><em>Sunday, June&nbsp;11</em></u>
								<br>
							</b>
							<br>
							Registration for the RallyCross takes place from 8am to 9am at Thunderhill 
							Park, and racing is scheduled from 9am to 5pm. <A href="http://www.sfrscca.org/RallyX/?faq">
								Click here</A> for more information regarding RallyCross.</font></p>
					<h2><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Registration and Entry 
							Information </font>
					</h2>
					<table width="506" border="1">
						<tr>
